5:
Is the base of the Resistance close
by?
9:
Yes, but we're not moving until the
sun goes down.
12:
An understandable precaution,
given the number of defeats you've
suffered.
15:
You have no right to judge us when
you've been hiding away like turtles
in your shell.
18:
A shell that we allowed to shatter.
Our paths shall be different from
here on out.
24:
A ruler must be, no matter the
circumstance.
27:
Well. Not all of us can afford to live
like a "ruler," high elf.
39:
Brrr, it is freezing! What I wouldn't do
for a fire right about now.
42:
The cold tonight is particularly
fierce. Perhaps we should ensure we
have enough food in our bellies to
keep warm...
46:
In that case, would you care to have
some elven pastries?
51:
You talkin' about those tiny
souvenir-sized morsels? How're we
supposed to fill up on that?
54:
Perhaps you should stop speaking
and use that mouth of yours to eat
a bite.
66: Damn... What'd you put in this?
70:
I can feel a heat burning in my
chest... Giving me strength.
84:
What, jealous that someone cooked
better than you?
89:
Not if they cheated! Forget sugar,
spice, and everything nice—only
magic could make something this
good!
97:
Speaking of cooking, I was
pleasantly surprised to see that
Shakari improved her culinary skills.
102:
Let me guess... 
She fed you her signature 
spicy roasted game meat?
108:
She sure did! Man, that was real
tasty too...
111:
I used to love eating it when I was a
child.
114:
Light, you journeyed together with
Shakari before, didn't you?
116:
What was she like when SHE was
younger?
123:
Put simply, she was a force to be
reckoned with.
129:
Well, she didn't have the physical
strength to swing a blade around.
131:
But her words were always sharper
than any blade, even back then. I
was not spared any biting remarks
despite being her senior.
133:
I can only imagine her trials over
these many years have tempered
her even further.
137:
You know, I've been wondering...
What exactly is Shakari to you, Lilith?
139:
You guys seem way closer than just
princess and retainer.
142:
We have lived in each other's
company since I was four years old.
145:
At the time, my parents had been
assassinated by fiends. My
grandmother would have taken me
in, but...
147:
In fear of further assassinations, the
royal family was split up and sent to
separate locations.
149:
She was a kind person, but not a
very strong one.
153:
And that's how you ended up with
the old hag, huh? Guess she's
strong, if nothing else.
156:
Despite what you might believe,
there were times when she wasn't
so harsh. She was different
whenever she spoke of Light and
Joshua.
158:
She would smile, sometimes sadly
and sometimes not... Even laugh
when the mood took her.
163:
Shakari hasn't had any of these
pastries yet, right?
165: Why don't you bring some to her?
170:
Shakari, perhaps you should take a
break—
178:
Damn it, that's coming from the
base!
187:
No! What kind of ruler would cower
while her citizens are in danger?!
195:
We elves are faster in the snow! We'll
escort people to safety!
